  "narrative": {
    "intro": "NAICS 611430 obligations in FY2026 to date total $339M across 1,742 awards, with an average award size of $195K. Obligations fell 57.7% year over year. Recent fiscal-year history shows peak obligations of $1B in FY24 and a decline to $802M in FY25 before the current-year total of $339M. The Department of Defense is the largest buyer in FY2026 to date at $168M, followed by the Department of the Interior at $51.2M and the Department of Homeland Security at $30.3M. The largest contractors so far this fiscal year include THE BOEING COMPANY at $61.5M and DEEP MILE NETWORKS LLC at $48.8M, with LEIDOS, INC. at $19M. The current-year totals are partial and reflect fiscal year to date activity rather than a complete fiscal year. Agencies and contractors listed reflect FY2026 to date rankings by obligations and may guide market engagement priorities for government contractors tracking federal spending on professional and management development training.",
    "sections": [
