        "body": "Obligations fell 57.7% year over year to $339M in FY2026 to date. This follows a decline from $1B in FY24 to $802M in FY25 and then to the current-year total of $339M. The average award size in FY2026 to date is $195K across 1,742 awards. Current-year totals are partial and reflect fiscal year to date activity."
      },
      {
        "heading": "Who are the largest buyers and contractors in FY2026 to date?",
        "body": "The Department of Defense leads buying at $168M, with the Department of the Interior at $51.2M and the Department of Homeland Security at $30.3M. THE BOEING COMPANY and DEEP MILE NETWORKS LLC are the largest vendors at $61.5M and $48.8M respectively, followed by LEIDOS, INC. at $19M. The top buying agencies and top vendors list reflects FY2026 to date obligations."
